      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstrated that the simulated QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) directly maps to the clinical decision threshold and is sensitive to model inputs.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the correct QoI and is clinically relevant, but sensitivity of NIH to inlet turbulence boundary conditions has not been formally demonstrated. Achieved level 2 falls one gradation short."
